			<!-- A propos -->
		
				<h3>About Me</h3>
			
				<p>I'm currently doing my final year undergraduate at <a href="http://www.nitk.ac.in" target="_blank"style="color: green">NITK Surathkal</a>, with a major in Electrical and Electronics Engineering. I am interested in doing research in Computer Vision and Artificial Intelligence. I have previously worked with <a href="http://www.ee.iisc.ac.in/new/people/faculty/soma.biswas/index.html"style="color: green"target="_blank">Prof Soma Biswas</a> at Electrical Department, IISc, Bangalore on Action Recognition from Skeletal Joints of Kinect Sensor. I interned at INRIA, France under <a href="http://www-sop.inria.fr/members/Francois.Bremond/"style="color: green"target="_blank">Francois Bremond</a> and worked on large scale activity recognition from RGBD data using Deep Learning. I am currently doing my bachelor's thesis under the supervision of <a href="http://www.ee.iisc.ac.in/new/people/faculty/soma.biswas/index.html"style="color: green"target="_blank">Prof Soma Biswas</a>, on motion preserving image representation of a video for video analysis tasks like Action recognition. Apart from research in core computer vision and AI, I am also interested in applying Machine Learning and Computer Vision techniques to 'out-of-the-box' problems like Selfie Detection and Personality based Scenario Response Prediction.
In my free time, I like to read novels - especially thrillers like The day of the Jackal and Killing Floor, and write chunks of prose and poetry, some of which can be found in my <a href="http://www.yashasannadaniblog.wordpress.com"style="color: green"target="_blank">blog</a>. In addition, I like to travel a lot, and hope to discover the marvels across all parts of the globe.  </p>
			</div>
			
		
		
